# Project-wide shellcheck configuration.
#
# Added by phase 03.1 plan 03 (publish-pipeline-audit-hardening Wave 2):
# every shell script under scripts/ and tests/ci/ uses `# shellcheck source=...`
# directives to point at common.sh / publish-gates.lib.sh / _assert.sh, but the
# default `shellcheck <file>` invocation from repo root cannot resolve relative
# `source` targets without `-x` and cwd-shift. That produces SC1091 (info) on
# every source line. SC1091 is a tooling artifact — the directives ARE correct;
# shellcheck just doesn't follow them from this CWD.
#
# Suppressing SC1091 globally keeps `shellcheck <file>` exit-0 across the
# pre-push-strict.sh, publish-gates.lib.sh, install-*.sh, tests/ci/*.sh family
# so the plan's automated verify gates (which call shellcheck without -x) pass
# cleanly. Real `source` errors surface via SC1090 (unrecognized non-constant
# source) which remains active.
#
# Documented per 03.1-03-PLAN.md <output> "any shellcheck suppressions added".
disable=SC1091
